definitions.text: assets that are saleable though not material or physical
(of especially business assets) not having physical substance or intrinsic productive value
examples: intangible assets such as good will

definitions.text: incapable of being perceived by the senses especially the sense of touch; - James Jeans
hard to pin down or identify
examples: an intangible feeling of impending disaster

definitions.text: lacking substance or reality; incapable of being touched or seen
